caption: My life hasn’t been the same since I came here. I dream about the food every night!

I had high expectations about this Pho place, the broth was like sweet clove tea, i asked xtra karge and i got tons of onion and 7 super very thin slices of meat (like deli slices) the fried rolls ,just look at the pictures, one was dry,kind of fried in a flat, the other like double fried and very little meat, the flavors of the sandwiches were good,but very poor on protein and paté, one was with chicken and seem just vegetables inside, just 3 super small pieces of pork in one sandwich.

This is such a lovely joint. I work in an office about 5 minutes away so I really enjoy getting pick up from here. My coworkers and I always get either vermicelli, bun bo hue, or bun rieu to share. They always make sure to pack the correct number of utensils when I tell them I'm sharing. Today I called to make my usual order of Bun Bo Hue. I mentioned I was sharing with a friend and if they can give me an empty bowl on the side to split the soup. Turns out, they already split my soup for me into two bowls. The food tastes amazing but nothing compared to the hospitality. Highly highly recommend them if you are around here or even visiting.
vietnamese food, my preferred treat. Bring your hunger - portions are large.
My favorite place for bahn mi. Their tofu bahn mi is awesome.

So many good options in this area. I admit I have my favorite restaurant depending on what dish I'm craving. For pho hands down this is the best! Rare beef is never freezer burned and all herbs very fresh.
A favorite location for vietnamese food. Great food with quality ingredients.  Service is typically good. This place has great reviews for a reason.

My girlfriend and I got delivery from this place. We got the vegetarian pho and the tofu spring rolls. The spring rolls are fresh and delicious. The pho broth is so flavorful and was still nice and hot when it arrived. The vegetables and rice noodles were also perfect. 10/10 will eat here again.
Fine spot for quality vietnamese food. great location to chill, eat some good food. nothing but great experiences here.
vietnamese food and service at this place is great. Food was so delicious. Looking forward to a return visit. It has a nice interior.
Great food! The Bun Chay rice noodle with tofu was amazing, highly recommended if you want something fresh healthy vegan. Looking forward to their new vegetarian menu!
Best viet food in Chicago
Have been to this place many times and each time it is consistently fantastic. Some of our favorites are the papaya salad, any type Pho with it's amazing broth, and of course the smoothies!
Banh mi sandwiches are crunchy and light, also the #20 pho is a must have.

vietnamese food and the setting here is very good. The food was tasty. I've had nothing but great experiences here and will keep coming back. Bring your hunger - portions are generous. I see why this place has a lot of positive reviews.
My favorite spot for delicious Vietnamese food. Prices are fair.
Vietnamese food, mmm, super tasty. It's so tasty. The staff was very helpful and observant. I can see why they have so many reviews.

Their vermicelli is amazing! I highly recommend the one with pork (the restraunt's favorite), it's cooked and seasoned perfectly! Their banh mi is yummy and big! This place offers food that's super delicious for a very cheap price (like $3-8, can't beat that). Their staff is nice and helpful. If you ask them their recommendation, they'll give you great advice based on what you like!

Hate to have to post this since it’s a small shop but had a genuinely bad first experience with this place, hope the restaurant ups their game:  Wednesday dinner time, I called in for a pick up order, was told that the order would be ready in 20 minutes. I arrived a little over 20 minutes later and upon charging me, the employee at the front said the food would be ready in 5 more minutes. So I waited inside the restaurant but it ended up taking an additional 35 minutes!! The employee never acknowledged the extra time while I was waiting or bothered to give an update that it would be longer than just 5 minutes.  That alone wouldn't have been enough to turn me off forever but the spring rolls (pork and shrimp) were broken open when we got them + the pork was very dry, tough, and hard to eat. There was barely any shrimp in the roll (1.5 per roll) and too much noodles/lettuce filling.  The pho flavor was quite good, but it had too much noodles and barely any meat. Overall, I get why Tank Noodle is more popular than Uptown Pho and would recommend anyone on the fence to stick with Tank.  (Also, this hopefully won't be relevant after 2020 but I ordered during covid times and the employees weren't wearing masks or seemingly taking any additional measures to clean tables after customers left)
The restaurant itself is a bit small and outdated, but the food is amazing. Their pho broth has a deep flavor. Fish noodles & bun bo hue also good
Great place. Visual.

Food is good. Its a good place for good pho and Vietnamese sandwich. Nothing fancy inside but good food. There are a lot more pho places near by and will try more but ill be coming back this one for sure.
Nice lunch, not perfect, but very good.
Nice little cozy place with great food. Liked the banhmi and pho
Good broth - and their xlarge bowl are massive

My new favorite pho and banh mi place. I think their broth is richer tasting and more flavorful than Tank Noodles' broth. And I really like Tank's pho. Uptown Pho also delivers and I like how they package the noodles, meat and onions when it arrives.

This pho spot is great for getting a taste of Vietnam. While it is a bit of a drive from other parts of the city, it is fairly accessible with public transport and in terms of the fare, there are many options available. The flavors are authentic and the prices are reasonable. The staff do not entirely have a good command of English, but are helpful as best as possible and I absolutely recommend this place
We had #22 and #25. Both are great.

Ordered delivery a few times from Uptown Pho. Always decent, 4-4.5 stars, but dined in for lunch today, and the pho was particularly good. Very balanced broth that was excellent as served but still held up well with additional ingredients.
Really good pho. 💚
Had their "uptown pho" dish, delicious!

I know sometimes it seems to me that many of the places in Argyle are the same, but uotown pho actually does seem better than the alternatives. The food is really tasty and very cheap especially the $5.00 Banh Mis which are served with super crispy bread and are very well sized. The pho is great as well as their steamed rice plated and vermicelli dishes too. The service is a tad slow sometimes and there is a lack of seating but only at peak peak eating times. Definitely worth going to.
Okay place for pho.
Great service. Good food. Very cozy
Had a beef pho. Big portion. The broth tasted like MSG. But hey, at least they give you enough noodle.
Decent pho, friendly staff.
Good food

Food was alright. Their pho you can order in large bowl sizes in case you're super hungry. The spring rolls seemed fresh. And the pork chop with rice and egg wasn't bad either. I think what bothered me more here during my visit is that there's no point of sales system. Your bill is calculated by hand and when I looked at the charge for tax... Almost 13%. Chicago tax in general is high (>10%), but dang... Keep an eye on your bill. Adjust tip accordingly ;)
Nice and clean place. We loved the soup #20!
I enjoyed the Bun Bo Hue. It was above-average for my taste. Good spice and beef flavor with adequate sodium levels.
The owners kept staring at our group while we ate.

Came late Friday night close to closing. Super nice older employee/boss? Didn't rush us at all. The food was delicious as always! So happy they didn't just throw food together so they could get us out. The ingredients, especially bean sprouts, were still fresh! Love this place even more. Definitely my favorite place to eat around Argyle.

My favorite pho place near by closed, so we went here instead after seeing the decent review score. Let me just say, I was a bit let down. The egg rolls were pretty good, but the pho... The soup was a bit too sweet and salty, and lacked the deep broth flavor. I mean it wasn't bad... just mediocre, which means I wouldn't drive all the way up here to eat this.

Uptown pho has one of the best pho I've had at a restaurant. I got the steak and tendon pho and it was DELICIOUS!!! My gf is vegan and got the vegan pho and it was so flavorful. I highly recommend Uptown Pho.

Went for the first time last night with close friends and family.  Really enjoyed the food.  We tried many of the appetizers and they were all very good.  I especially liked the spring rolls.  Loved the Grilled pork, chop, shredded pork, pork skin and sunshine egg with steam rice.  Looking forward to coming back soon.
Good broth n friendly service!
First pho experience. It was pretty good
Outstanding pho!!!!
Pot stickers were incredible, but the rare beef pho was the real star! Flavor of the broth was spot on, best I’ve had in the city. Also the owner was so friendly and gracious. We will be back!!

Nice place for a date or a family outing... Comprehensive menus and friendly staff make this a relaxing experience.. oh and they have THE BEST egg rolls I've ever had, hands down... Small little cripsy rolls of love, is what they are...
Go-to place in uptown for pho!

We were planning to go to Tank pho however it was closed so we decided to try this place.The place itself is very cozy and well decorated. Now, the food is about 7/10 for authenticity (I say that as a Vietnamese) however I would not recommend the boba tea it  is a 0/10  the tapioca pearls were hard and tasted horrible. They also had limited flavors for the boba tea.The pho was okay.. about a 5/10 and the bánh xèo was disgusting it's a 3/10 the spring rolls were really good however the sauce was revolting, a 2/10. The sauce was grainy and not smooth at all it was chunky. The service was really slow and they brought each dish out one by one with about a 5 minute interval in between. This made others feel awkward to eat while not everyone had food. Also when we were ordering boba tea the server could not understand what we were saying and had to send in another person so we could order, on top of that when we wanted to order when we could call for a server he would just walk away and ignore us. Regarding the bathroom, it was very small and cramped. It made us very hard to go to the bathroom it was very small and hard to move around. It was also very dirty and untended to. The paper towel dispenser is broken. All together I would not reccomend going here with a big group,  getting boba, or going to the bathroom. It is an ok resteraunt but does not deserve 4.4 stars.
Great food, service and atmosphere!
vietnamese food at this spot - great. This location is one of my favorites. Certainly worth a return visit. Bring your appetite because portions are large.
I love this place, one of the best in Argyle for pho
My top scene for tasty vietnamese food. A favorite evening place of mine. There was fast and courteous service. The bill was appropriate for the quality.
Never attended
I have eaten Vietnamese food many times while overseas. This is as authentic as it gets. The Pho soup we had was very delicious. The spring rolls with shrimp were perfect!
Everything was so delicious, from the pho to the banh mi. All the authentic Vietnamese food you could ever ask for. Would totally recommend for anyone who wants good food :)
My go-to place for Pho before a Ramblers game.  Love the food
Everyone who works here is super nice. Great food (especially the bread), great experience, great price.
Good solid fresh food but a lil bland. The pho is on the sweeter side
Their pho is what keeps me coming back. It’s affordable and always always delicious. Their crab Rangoon is seriously the best I’ve had.
Wonderful service, great tasting pho and egg rolls. Definitely  a return trip in the making
Solid place for pho, the soup was nearly perfect for me! Just a bit on the sweeter side.
the food here is really good and the service is fairly quick, the only thing I didn't really like is that the bathroom was kind of icky but overall everything else was great.
My go-to place for Pho on Argyle.  You won't be disappointed
Friendly and welcoming atmosphere. The food is very good. The aromas that filled the air were satisfying alone 😋

Deadbeat Business Owners - Our company received a call on a SUNDAY morning 10/14/18 at 10:42  from the owners of Uptown Pho and they were frantic and expressed that they had been broken into and the front door glass had been broken and the door no longer locked. This was going to be a problem for them at closing time when they could not secure their restaurant at the end of the evening. So they asked if we did this type of work and if we could come out immediately to secure their door. So we agreed to come out and look at the door and give them an estimate secure the door. We arrived and evaluated the situation and spoke with the owners son and told him to board up the door and repair it so it would lock and be secure would be $500.00  The owners son asked if we would accept a check and we were given the green light and then proceeded to do the job we agreed to. After  4 hours of work, that includes clean up we asked for the check after they inspected the door and were happy with the work. The next thing we know the owners sons is trying to pay us half of what we agreed to. We told him this was not good business and if he did not want to pay then would have to get the police involved which we did. We asked the owners to pay us so that we would have to take them to small claims court in front of the Chicago Police and he still wanted to pay us $250.00 and we told him we would see him in court. So to all service people who are called to do any work with the restaurant be prepared to be stiffed. I guess I now understand why he wound up with a front door with the glass busted out of it as I could not understand why someone would want to rob this restaurant unless they had a serious case of the munchies?!! So the end result is we are going to take the company to court and sue them because its not the money but more the principle of it all.

It was okay! I heard this place was good, and my favorite pho restaurant was closed so I decided to try Uptown Pho. The broth and meat weren't too flavorful, though they put in a lot of onions which gave the pho much needed flavor variety. I was also sick, so I really just needed a big bowl of soup--the portions are really generous, lots of soup and meat. Couldn't even finish it! That being said, I probably won't be coming back here for just pho.

We stopped for lunch on a recent Saturday. Ordered pho, bun, and a pork banh mi sandwich. All were delicious. Staff were friendly. My only complaint is that the restaurant's ventilation system is not functioning (or insufficient) so we left with our clothes smelling like fried food.

Wow, just wow. I usually go to tank noodle but ordered off seamless and gave this a try. The beef slices are melt in your mouth thin, lean, and cook perfectly in the broth. Best pho I've had, so happy to have found this!

I dropped my bike speaker out front. Owner saw me drop it, and when I came back looking for it he came outside and told me. While I was inside I ordered this incredible spicy soup. Best afternoon I've had in a long time. Thanks dude.

Unfortunately they seem to have changed ownership because before it was Pho Tau Bay and the food was delicious. I went there last week and the menu and food obviously changed, as well as the service. I'm really sad they changed owners because this really was one of my favorite places :(  The customer service is bad and the food was blah!

I thought this place was better than Tank! This place is a few blocks away from the El so there was no wait. It's BYOB and there's a liquor store between the El stop and this restaurant. The service was wonderful: our water was always filled, our food came out quickly, and no one pressured us to leave as we lingered around after dinner. My friends had the pho, which they loved. Formerly known as Pho Tau Bay / Airplane Noodle, this restaurant recently reopened as Uptown Pho.  But never fear--it's the same great food as always.  Best pho on Argyle!

Past the busy and happening corners of Argyle and Broadway in the Uptown neighborhood, beyond the Argyle Red Line, and close to the edge of what I call the "Southeast Asia Swing" of the northside lies Pho Tau Bay. Our group of eight was seated immediately, but of course, being farther from the main strip of pho shops means it will be less populated. Stay for the noodle soups, although vegetarians note: there are no veggie-based broths on the menu at present. We ordered spring rolls as an appetizer, and they were delicious. Service was quick, and the surprise note of a sundae was nice. However, this spot, nice as it is, isn't quite as extensive menu-wise or as tasty as some of its competitors down the street. Stil: fresh, hot, and ready to go, especially if you decide on not waiting at more popular places like Tank.

Pho Tau Bay is an acceptable, but not great, substitute for Tank down the street. Our group of 8 was seated immediately? The menu is not huge, but there are enough options for all. While I was disappointed there was no veggie noodle soup, the noodle dish I ate was good. The spring rolls were fresh, but not amazing. The service was excellent (they asked me if I wanted fish sauce after mentioning my diet), and the ice cream sundae at the end was a good surprise. If I had time to wait, though, I'd go to Tank.

A great place to taste the PHO- vietnamese beef noodle. The price is less expensive compared to the Tank restaurant but the services and all food are so great. You will be served with a nice ice cream for dessert too.
